274
00:14:53,220 --> 00:14:56,400
I didn't know before he told me, father.

275
00:14:56,400 --> 00:15:01,075
I never had trouble talking to him.

276
00:15:01,075 --> 00:15:04,075
I actually learned a lot from him.

277
00:15:04,075 --> 00:15:07,425
He read lots of books to overcome it,

278
00:15:07,425 --> 00:15:12,600
and he grew up to be a really decent guy.

279
00:15:12,600 --> 00:15:19,850
Father, what college he attended isn't important compared to how he's lived.

280
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:24,025
The size of his house isn't important compared to how great his character is.

281
00:15:24,025 --> 00:15:25,875
Those things are more important to me.

282
00:15:25,875 --> 00:15:29,175
Not having a college degree isn't a problem.

283
00:15:29,170 --> 00:15:31,775
I'm not talking about the degree.

284
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:37,700
They don't just teach knowledge at school.

285
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:43,775
Why do you think people attend 16 years of school?

286
